<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="266" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,828,1476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,490,828,853]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Coloration and morphology.</emphasis>
Ground colour yellow (
<figureCitation box="[761,851,828,853]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,196,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrosteles parafalcatus sp. nov. A. habitus, dOrsal view; B. face; C. habitus, lateral view; D. habitus, anteriOr view; E. pygOfer, lateral view; F. pygOfer, ventral view; G. male 2nd abdOminal tergites, dOrsal view; H. male 2nd abdOminal sternal apOdemes, dOrsal view; I–J. male 1st abdOminal sternal apOdeme, dOrsO-anteriOr and anteriOr view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441603/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Crown with pair of dark spots at posterior margin, pair of dark transverse streaks present at the anterior margin interrupted medially but forming transverse dark band between eyes and ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[433,558,900,925]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,196,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrosteles parafalcatus sp. nov. A. habitus, dOrsal view; B. face; C. habitus, lateral view; D. habitus, anteriOr view; E. pygOfer, lateral view; F. pygOfer, ventral view; G. male 2nd abdOminal tergites, dOrsal view; H. male 2nd abdOminal sternal apOdemes, dOrsal view; I–J. male 1st abdOminal sternal apOdeme, dOrsO-anteriOr and anteriOr view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441603/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Fig. 5A, D</figureCitation>
). Forewing with yellowish brown tint (
<figureCitation box="[995,1084,900,925]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,196,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrosteles parafalcatus sp. nov. A. habitus, dOrsal view; B. face; C. habitus, lateral view; D. habitus, anteriOr view; E. pygOfer, lateral view; F. pygOfer, ventral view; G. male 2nd abdOminal tergites, dOrsal view; H. male 2nd abdOminal sternal apOdemes, dOrsal view; I–J. male 1st abdOminal sternal apOdeme, dOrsO-anteriOr and anteriOr view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441603/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,828,1476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,385,938,963]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Male abdomen.</emphasis>
Male 2nd acrotergite with trunk V-shaped, anterior processes broad; neck slender, longer than half of trunk width. 2nd tergal apodeme developed, reaching margin of tergite posteriorly. 1 
<taxonomicName box="[1176,1270,973,1002]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="sternal">st sternal</taxonomicName>
apodeme with posterior lobes rounded, almost as long as basal width. 2nd sternal apodeme developed with posterior lobes about 1.5X as long as basal width, extending beyond sternum margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,828,1476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,384,1088,1113]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer lobe broad, with comb-like tubercle at caudo-ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1251,1345,1088,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[181,1405,196,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[181,1405,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrosteles parafalcatus sp. nov. A. habitus, dOrsal view; B. face; C. habitus, lateral view; D. habitus, anteriOr view; E. pygOfer, lateral view; F. pygOfer, ventral view; G. male 2nd abdOminal tergites, dOrsal view; H. male 2nd abdOminal sternal apOdemes, dOrsal view; I–J. male 1st abdOminal sternal apOdeme, dOrsO-anteriOr and anteriOr view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441603/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular (
<figureCitation box="[277,370,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1888,1910]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,280,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,258,1805]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrosteles parafalcatus sp. nov. A. valve, subgenital plate, style and cOnnective, dOrsal view; B. aedeagus, ventral view; C. aedeagus, lateral view; Macrosteles indrinus (Pruthi) D. pygOfer, lateral view; E. pygOfer, caudal view; F. valve, subgenital plate, style and cOnnective, dOrsal view; G. aedeagus, lateral view; H. aedeagus, dOrsal view; I. abdOminal apOdemes (ReprOduced frOm Khatri &amp; Webb, 2010)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441605/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped, with stem almost equal to arms in length (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1235,1124,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1888,1910]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,280,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,258,1805]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrosteles parafalcatus sp. nov. A. valve, subgenital plate, style and cOnnective, dOrsal view; B. aedeagus, ventral view; C. aedeagus, lateral view; Macrosteles indrinus (Pruthi) D. pygOfer, lateral view; E. pygOfer, caudal view; F. valve, subgenital plate, style and cOnnective, dOrsal view; G. aedeagus, lateral view; H. aedeagus, dOrsal view; I. abdOminal apOdemes (ReprOduced frOm Khatri &amp; Webb, 2010)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441605/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Style apophysis truncate, preapical lobe moderately developed (
<figureCitation box="[690,781,1160,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1888,1910]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,280,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,258,1805]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrosteles parafalcatus sp. nov. A. valve, subgenital plate, style and cOnnective, dOrsal view; B. aedeagus, ventral view; C. aedeagus, lateral view; Macrosteles indrinus (Pruthi) D. pygOfer, lateral view; E. pygOfer, caudal view; F. valve, subgenital plate, style and cOnnective, dOrsal view; G. aedeagus, lateral view; H. aedeagus, dOrsal view; I. abdOminal apOdemes (ReprOduced frOm Khatri &amp; Webb, 2010)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441605/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft slender, smooth, with apical appendages moderately long, evenly curved dorsally, sickle-shaped in lateral view, in posterior view forming narrow V-shaped apex (
<figureCitation box="[219,341,1232,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1888,1910]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,280,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,258,1805]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Macrosteles parafalcatus sp. nov. A. valve, subgenital plate, style and cOnnective, dOrsal view; B. aedeagus, ventral view; C. aedeagus, lateral view; Macrosteles indrinus (Pruthi) D. pygOfer, lateral view; E. pygOfer, caudal view; F. valve, subgenital plate, style and cOnnective, dOrsal view; G. aedeagus, lateral view; H. aedeagus, dOrsal view; I. abdOminal apOdemes (ReprOduced frOm Khatri &amp; Webb, 2010)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1441605/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Fig. 6B–C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
