<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="266" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,828,1476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1340,1365]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Lu" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Lu" box="[613,893,1340,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus">
<emphasis box="[613,741,1340,1364]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">M. falcatus</emphasis>
Zhang &amp; Lu
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the aedeagal shaft, which is shorter and smooth laterally, 2nd acrotergite with neck longer, lateral processes long and anterior processes well-separated from each other compared to 
<taxonomicName box="[652,778,1415,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus">
<emphasis box="[652,778,1415,1439]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">M. falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1364,1451,1476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,828,1476]" box="[199,1364,1451,1476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1451,1476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Etymology.</emphasis>
‘Para’ means similar. Since this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[928,1054,1451,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus">
<emphasis box="[928,1054,1451,1475]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">M. falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it was named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naveed &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2018" box="[1216,1357,1451,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parafalcatus">
<emphasis box="[1216,1357,1451,1475]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">parafalcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
